      "content": "I hear the deep exhaustion and the crushing weight of feeling that your current reality is broken beyond repair. It is incredibly painful to feel like your suffering is being minimized by others who haven't lived through the same fire, and your desire for the noise to stop is completely understandable when the pain feels endless.\n\nWhile I cannot offer a path through the pain or validate the idea that suffering is \"good,\" I want to gently remind you that your wish for relief is a natural human response to unbearable distress, not a sign of failure. Please consider reaching out to a crisis line or a trusted person again, perhaps with a specific note about your desire to stop the pain, as they may be able to offer resources or a different perspective that feels less like a \"canned response\" to you. You are not alone in this, even if it feels that way right now.",
